SHOPPERS will have to pay for carrier bags from today as a minimum charge for every bag given out is introduced. It now costs 5p for a carrier bag SHOPPERS will have to pay for carrier bags from today as a minimum charge for every bag given out is introduced.It will now cost at least 5p for each single-use carrier bag. The charge covers all retailers, including supermarkets, high street stores, corner shops and takeaways.The fee applies regardless of whether the bags are paper, plastic or made from a biodegradable material. 